@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="privacy-container">
    <h1>Privacy Policy for iDesignElectrotech</h1>
        <p><em>Last Updated: March 13, 2025</em></p>

        <p>
            At iDesignElectrotech (<a href="https://www.idesignelectrotech.com">www.idesignelectrotech.com</a>), 
            we are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, 
            disclose, and safeguard your personal information when you use our website and services, 
            including our electrical circuit simulator. This policy aligns with the Australian Privacy 
            Principles (APPs) under the Privacy Act 1988.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We may collect the following types of information:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Personal Information</strong>: If you create an account, we may collect your name, 
            email address, and any other details you provide.</li>
            <li><strong>Usage Data</strong>: We collect anonymized data about how you interact with the 
            site (e.g., pages visited, time spent) to improve our services.</li>
            <li><strong>Circuit Designs</strong>: If you save a design in the simulator, we store it to 
            allow you to access it later.</li>
            <li><strong>Cookies</strong>: We use cookies to enhance your experience (e.g., remembering 
            login sessions). You can disable cookies in your browser, but some features may not work.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use your information to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Provide and improve the website and simulator.</li>
            <li>Save and retrieve your circuit designs.</li>
            <li>Communicate with you (e.g., support requests or updates).</li>
            <li>Analyze usage trends to enhance learning resources.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. How We Share Your Information</h2>
        <p>
            We do not sell or share your personal information with third parties, except:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>With your consent.</li>
            <li>To comply with legal obligations (e.g., Australian law).</li>
            <li>With service providers (e.g., hosting on DigitalOcean) who are bound to protect your data.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Data Storage and Security</h2>
        <p>
            Your data is stored on secure servers hosted by DigitalOcean. We use industry-standard 
            encryption and security measures, but no system is 100% secure. Please report any concerns 
            to <a href="mailto:[insert contact email]">[insert contact email]</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>Under Australian law, you can:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Access or correct your personal information.</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your data (subject to legal retention requirements).</li>
            <li>Opt out of communications.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            Contact us at <a href="mailto:[insert contact email]">[insert contact email]</a> to exercise 
            these rights.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Children’s Privacy</h2>
        <p>
            Our site is designed for students, including those under 18. We do not knowingly collect 
            personal information from children under 13 without parental consent. If you’re a parent or 
            guardian and believe we’ve collected such data, contact us immediately.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Third-Party Links</h2>
        <p>
            Our site may link to external resources. We’re not responsible for their privacy practices.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
            We may update this policy as the site evolves. Check back here for the latest version.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
            Questions? Reach out at <a href="mailto:[insert contact email]">[insert contact email]</a>.
        </p>
